IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO MATCH RESIDENCY AND FELLOWSHIP APPLICANTS WITH TRAINING PROGRAMS OF THEIR CHOICE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO MATCH HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS TO GRADUATE MEDICAL EDUCATION AND ADVANCED TRAINING PROGRAMS THROUGH A PROCESS THAT IS FAIR, EFFICIENT, TRANSPARENT, AND RELIABLE. TO PROVIDE MEANINGFUL AND ACCESSIBLE MATCH DATA AND ANALYSIS TO STAKEHOLDERS.
IRS990.Desc: HEALTH PROFESSIONS MATCHING PROGRAM - ORGANIZE AND CONDUCT A NATIONAL CLEARING HOUSE TO MATCH PHYSICIANS AND OTHER HEALTH PROFESSIONS APPLICANTS WITH GRADUATE EDUCATION PROGRAMS OF THEIR CHOICE. FOR FISCAL YEAR 2018, THERE WERE 41,235 RESIDENCY AND FELLOWHIP PHYSICIAN APPLICANTS MATCHED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A DRAFT OF THE FORM 990 WILL BE PROVIDED TO EACH MEMBER OF THE BOARD FOR REVIEW AND TO REQUEST CHANGES PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EACH DIRECTOR, PRINCIPAL OFFICER AND MEMBER OF A COMMITTEE WITH GOVERNING BOARD DELEGATED POWERS SHALL ANNUALLY SIGN A STATEMENT SUBSTANTIALLY IN THE FORM ATTACHED HERETO WHICH AFFIRMS SUCH PERSON: A) HAS RECEIVED A COPY OF THE CONFLICTS OF INTEREST POLICY; B) HAS READ AND UNDERSTANDS THE POLICY; C) HAS AGREED TO COMPLY WITH THE POLICY; AND D) UNDERSTANDS NATIONAL RESIDENT MATCHING PROGRAM IS CHARITABLE AND IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN ITS FEDERAL TAX EXEMPTION IT MUST ENGAGE PRIMARILY IN ACTIVITIES WHICH ACCOMPLISH ONE OR MORE OF ITS TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT'S SALARY, SALARY INCREASES, BENEFITS AND/OR BONUSES SHALL BE SET FORTH BY A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE COMPRISED OF THE CHAIR, CHAIR ELECT, AND PAST CHAIR OF THE BOARD OF THE NATIONAL RESIDENT MATCHING PROGRAM. A MARKET PRICING ANALYSIS WAS PERFORMED BY NONPROFIT HR TO DETERMINE RECOMMENDED SALARY RANGES AND MERIT MATRIX STRUCTURES. THEY ANALYZED JOB CONTENT DATA AND CONDUCTED A MARKET PAY ANALYSIS, BENCHMARKING OTHER NON-PROFITS AND THE WASHINGTON D.C. AREA WITH A SIMILAR BUDGET SIZE TO DEVELOP COMPETITIVE MARKET PAY RATES. IT WAS LAST REVIEWED IN 2018.
